Murray's promotion means he faces an easier draw in the last 16 against an opponent seeded between nine and 12.

Potential last-16 opponents include Latvian Ernests Gulbis or Frenchman Richard Gasquet, rather than big-serving Canadian Milos Raonic or his Wimbledon conqueror Grigor Dimitrov. 

Top seed Novak Djokovic is projected to meet Roger Federer in the final, the Swiss also benefiting from Nadal's withdrawal as he replaced the Spaniard as the No 2 seed.

